
  Name:  mblen
  
  #include <stdlib.h>
  int mblen(const char *str, size_t size);
  
  The mblen( ) function returns the length (in bytes) of a 
  multibyte character pointed to by str. Only the first size 
  number of characters are examined. It returns on error.
  
  Example:
  printf("%d", mblen(mb, 2));
  
  Related Functions : mbtowc and wctomb
